[The etiology of this presumed waterborne outbreak of hepatitis is not stated but is likely to be either type A or E. If the cases are primarily in adults and if there are fatalities in pregnant women, type E viral hepatitis is likely the cause.

Maps of India can be seen at http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4722930,57327. Odisha is one of the 29 states of India, located in the east of the country. It is surrounded by the states of West Bengal to the northeast, Jharkhand to the north, Chhattisgarh to the west and northwest, and Andhra Pradesh to the south and southwest, and can be found on a map at: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Odisha. - Mod.LL]
